{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"f6lwf3ytkd2f80adq6eluvv","title":"Objects lifecycle in memory","desc":"","updated":1713807836105,"created":1713720801067,"custom":{},"fname":"lang.java.jre.memory.lifecycle.objects","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"c26ef06a62188d0254121e230456a59b","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.jre.memory.lifecycle.objects","id":"f6lwf3ytkd2f80adq6eluvv","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.jre.memory.heap","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":30,"offset":378},"end":{"line":14,"column":59,"offset":407},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.jre.memory.heap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"lang.java.jre.memory.lifecycle.objects","id":"f6lwf3ytkd2f80adq6eluvv","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"lang.java.jre.memory.stack","position":{"start":{"line":14,"column":123,"offset":471},"end":{"line":14,"column":153,"offset":501},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"lang.java.jre.memory.stack"}}],"anchors":{},"children":["0o92h4fvq9qnmz2ujdcj534","dy15wqx49hkiq04x4mmf8q0"],"parent":"avnpfmt680rfny40cu072kp","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"objects-lifecycle-in-memory\">Objects lifecycle in memory<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#objects-lifecycle-in-memory\"></a></h1>\n<pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span> smallBox<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Unlike C++, the above statement won’t create an object. It will just create a reference variable. The reference variable has to be given an object.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span> smallBox<span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Now <code>smallBox</code> contains address of an object of Box class. That is, it points to the object. However, the object itself has no name.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Memory is allocated on the <a href=\"/cs/notes/f7m2c5b73rmo6b87s3e9zqa\">Heap Space</a> and a reference for that object is returned which is stored in <a href=\"/cs/notes/g1mrhzpjy5cyod1io4faf8k\">Stack</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/0o92h4fvq9qnmz2ujdcj534\">Reachable</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cs/notes/dy15wqx49hkiq04x4mmf8q0\">Root</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","title":"Computer Science","desc":"","updated":1715103618849,"created":1713296516553,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"cs"},"contentHash":"36faf26c6be438d4aed355d72b55a110","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"arch","position":{"start":{"line":6,"column":3,"offset":105},"end":{"line":6,"column":11,"offset":113},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"arch"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"7ncn3al6mmutkhgoesulce9","vaultName":"cs"},"value":"paradigm","position":{"start":{"line":11,"column":3,"offset":159},"end":{"line":11,"column":15,"offset":171},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"paradigm"}}],"anchors":{"references":{"type":"header","text":"References","value":"references","line":23,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["0xgibr34qhbv1edksyoxakk","t246wcci6dy9lnof7l1os4l","71sipcgr0pdqyxnmntvx28w","6k8qk8m6zofpfla0wr8eajn","szmkrtr9ezx1kg3mzcamb7m","a6m88ijp6ij9aam2ose0k6j","7t5m5bvvkqqmexze4ymednf","4bgqfqpix52j5ek9oawj3lw","ng2w78j1rxy1prvsi6zc9j3","q1uj4uy5892ahhlgrn1wi7m","qnetoavqu273jl4iovqtk76","qanoka2zolegyqtrlis4sg2","nsbtaj4zu6fmgjuooy55mbx","uc1prffatcsbivlbj2yud2i","azqmz08s69usdskj1a7v94c","v3e3a8biac8damd